questions.question: Asexual reproduction is best described as...

choices.answer: the creation of identical offspring from two parents.
the creation of different offspring from two parents.
the creation of different offspring from one parent.
the creation of identical offspring from one parent.

questions.question: Asexual reproduction is made through the process of

choices.answer: mitosis.
meiosis.
selective breeding.
genetic engineering.

questions.question: Asexual reproduction is used to make....

choices.answer: sperm and eggs.
new cells in the body.
ONLY bacteria.
single-celled organisms AND body cells.

questions.question: Sexual reproduction is best described as....

choices.answer: the creation of different offspring from two parents.
the creation of different offspring from one parent.
the creation of identical offspring from two parents.
the creation of identical offspring from one parent.
single-celled organisms.
identical clone cells.
sex cells (the sperm and egg).
spores.

questions.question: Sex cells are made through the process of....

choices.answer: mitosis.
meiosis.
genetic engineering.
selective breeding.

questions.question: An advantage of asexual reproduction is that....

choices.answer: the offspring have a lot of genetic diversity.
the offspring are different from the parents.
most large organisms reproduce this way.
it produces many offspring very quickly.

questions.question: An advantage of sexual reproduction is that....

choices.answer: it produces a lot of offspring very quickly.
the offspring produces are identical to the parent.
the offspring have very little genetic diversity.
the offspring are very genetically diverse.
